list.name: Default
list.comment:
* added: - update analyzed data refactored and work like charm - htmlAnalyzer and scriptAnalyzer now get hash values from database correctly
NOTE: if module consider that there no analysis to perform (i.e. page/script/etc. has same hash values), he MUST return dict['id'] = currentRowIdThatDoesntNeedToBeUpdated instead of dict of analyzed features

task.summary: Default task
* analyze functions config file + features config file optimization
* optimize queue info passing - if function result is int/float and equal to 0/0.0, just simply don't include result in queue

* now it's able to run every single function from every module in separate process added: - try-except wrappers - setters and getters for module activation in pyHTMLAnalyzer - delete redundant methods

* now it's able to create several processes in "getAllAnalyzeReport" functions in all modules // not really significantly improves speed, but it will, later, when script-module will be rewritten to analyze by pieces of script-code, not whole script, as it does now
* script analyzer now able to parallel analysis via pieces of script code, in limit - one process for one code piece Letter zero entropy value fix

* correct entropy calculation in case of rewritten script analyzer outcome (analyzed features per (has256, hash512)) also deleted parallelViaFunctions, cause now script analyzer produce outcome in such case: dict: ----- script piece1 - (hash256, hash512) - list of analyzed features for script piece1 ----- script piece2 - (hash256, hash512) - list of analyzed features for script piece2 ... ----- script pieceN - (hash256, hash512) - list of analyzed features for script pieceN
this output refactoring is essentially important, cause before performing analysis we must check, have we analyze this piece of code already (will be checked by pair of hashes)
* not analyzing page/script code piece if its hashes already exists in listOfHashes (this list must pass from outer function and must be got from database)
* SQLAlchemy integration - database creation, usage, drop; ORM-classes and corresponding tables creation via runtime methods and class creation and analyzeFunctions config-file
* now project is less specific to certain module and has ability to store all modules instances (also as ORM-classes) in one place (modulesRegister)
* class public variables turned into private, as it should be
* hot fix due to previous commit ("protected" attribute)
* logging
* another config-file parsing procedure: more common, allow more flexible and humanized formatting also: removed modules dependencies in databaseConnector page predefined utf-8 encoding fix
* extra (non-analysis) columns, extra (non-class) tables, table relations and foreign keys NOTE: currently not more than one foreign key per one column
* ORM-SUDI (select, update, delete, insert) methods

* - common names from config file in separate class with static fields - hashValues from database extract before analysis (htmlAnalyzer, scriptAnalyzer) - database connection data in config file so as this data extractor code inside classes (geoIPFunctions and pyHTMLAnalyzer) - pyHTMLAnalyzer insert/update analyzed data pre-commit, will be refactored soon

* insert analyzed data refactored and works like charm also: - from config file removed methods that return non String/Integer/Float values (will be improved later) - queue optimization (not pass values that is 0 or 0.0f) also removed and will be returned later - correct ORM class values printing

* added: - update analyzed data refactored and work like charm - htmlAnalyzer and scriptAnalyzer now get hash values from database correctly
NOTE: if module consider that there no analysis to perform (i.e. page/script/etc. has same hash values), he MUST return dict['id'] = currentRowIdThatDoesntNeedToBeUpdated instead of dict of analyzed features

* too many files in one commit, sadly - database types in config now ignore case (databaseConnector) - all functions output values like lists of dicts now serialized via JSON (pyHTMLAnalyzer) - multi-process fix (scriptAnalyzer, htmlAnalyzer) - additional logging
* bunch of annoying bugs fixed (more border, non-zero checks)
